transcript.text: Welcome to Onprint Shop At Onprint Shop, we are continuously evolving our solution capabilities to help you deliver the best services to your customers and grow your online business.
We are releasing Onprint Shop version 6.3 which includes new, future and enhancement to meet the changing requirements of our clients.
So these are the list of major upgrades.

The first one is custom size change from studio page product type wise, studio setting product wise, predefined message product type wise, language dereferences, page, background enhancement samples in text property panel, product unit wise, position and size controls, text alignment in PDF block, text block ruler guide and text outline and border.
So let's start with first one custom size change from studio page.

In this feature, the storefront customers will be able to change the size of custom size product directly from the designer studio so that every time they don't need to click on back button and change and see the size from the price calculator.
Let's see how it works in the designer studio.
They can change easily the custom size from over here so 10 by 10 and accordingly they will get the price calculator as well in the designer studio.
Now the.
Next one is product type wise studio setting in the admin panel.
In the designer studio setting currently we have an option to manage the designer studio setting for specific product.
But in the current upgrades we have included some more options from where the admin user will be able to manage the designers settings product type wise as well as product specific.
This is common product type specific and product specific Commons.
Whenever we change anything over here, it will apply for all products we have added to the stores.
The second one is product type specific so we can select the standard product, calendar, book, product, promotional product and custom size.
So it is product type specific and the next one is product specific.
Individually you can select any product and change the Designer Studio setting.
Now the next feature is.
Product wise predefined message.
In this feature admin can set the predefined message product wise.
Here they can select the any product and can set the predefined text for designer studio and then it will be available for storefront customers in the designer studio.
Now the next feature is.
Product type wise language text references.
Currently in the solution the admin can only define a general language text references common for all products for Designer studio.
But now in these upgrades we have introduced new feature where the admin will be able to define product type by language text references in the admin panel for the Designer studio here.
They can.
Select the product type like standard Calendar and then they can set the language text for the design studio.
Now the next feature is.

Page Background Enhancement In this feature the admin will be able to create a special section for background images and will be able to upload different images in all the category and on the front store in the background background tab only the images uploaded in the background image category will be displayed.
This is image and they will get the one tab as a background and here they can manage the categories and everything.
Then for the storefront customers, once they upload any image for the background, the storefront customer will be able to see the property panel for the background images.
We can change the brightness, adjust the image so filter option, rotate image, they can flip the image, they can set the opacity.
So this kind of features customer will be able to use.
Also, the customers will be able to view a pen icon for the background image as well, from where they will be able to easily move the image in the background.
Now the next feature is.
Symbols in text property panel.
There is a feature we have introduced where the storefront customers will be able to add symbols in the text box in Advanced Designer Studio.
The symbols will display only if selected font supports those symbols.
The admin also will have a provision to control the samples to be displayed in the property panel.
For the back end they can control special character.
Over here they can fix the character what they want to allow to front store customers and then front store customer can enter the special character like this.
Now the next feature is.
Product unit wise, position and size controls.

In this feature, the admin will be able to change the dimension displayed in the property panel for the element in the X axis and Y axis position and the height and width controls from pixel to match the product measurement unit or any measurement unit of the length.
Here they would be able to.
Change.
According their product pixels, inches, centimeter, MMM feet or meter.
Let's say if I change in inches and save it and in the designer studio if I select any shape or anything, let's select the shape and now I can change this XX and Y axis in inches.
Currently we have option to change in pixels only, but according to our product we can fix this in the back end and then.
Also they can change the weight and height.
Now the next feature is.
Text alignment in PDF block, Text block in the PDF block.
End user will be able to align the text block like that.
They can change the alignment to the left, centre, right.
It is for PDF Block Studio.
Now the next feature is.

Roller Guide For Roller Guide, we have introduced a new feature where the admin and the storefront customers will be able to add the multiple reference roller guides in the canvas in the designer studio while creating the template.
They can use the multiple roller guide like this vertically, horizontally.
So it would be easier than to create the templates and have the proper shape.
Now the next feature.
Is text outline and border.
In this feature, the end customer will be able to set the border of the text itself.
Click on add new text.
Enter the text.
This is stock and this is border.
They can choose the border colour, border size and stock colour, stock size like that.
OK, so these were our major upgrades for Designer Studio version 6.3.
In case you could not find what you are looking for, please e-mail us at support at onprintshop com and we will add them in the suggestion list.
Thank you.
